race.comment: PALLADIUM (7) was unwanted in betting on debut last start but ran a strong race, finishing third and beaten a long neck over 1300m at Wangaratta. Can open his winning account this time. WINMAR (13) missed the placings first up recently but was not too far from the winner when fifth over 1207m at Geelong. Won't find this as tough. Should be involved in the finish. A recent Seymour jumpout win makes us think NEVILLE BARTOS (6) is the pick of the first-starters and can get in the money, or should I say cash, on debut. VERY TORQUEE (9) was beaten in a photo last start, which followed a nice debut, so there's no reason with the benefit of those runs under the belt he can't score a deserved win here. CARRAMAR (3) won a jumpout two back and although third in a recent trial, he wasn't beaten that far. Blinkers on for the debut and drawn nicely so reluctant to dismiss.
